When she lost the race many, including myself, were heartbroken. It was a deeply hurtful experience, especially because of all the effort she had put in new voter registration though her grassroots organisation, The New Georgia Project, which she founded in 2013.
Sacrifice
 It appeared that all the hard work and sacrifice had come to a screeching halt. Instead of disappearing into the shadows, Ms Abrams ruminated over her loss and then decided to keep going. “I sat Shiva for 10 days… then I started plotting,” she says in a profile published in the Vogue.
After her loss, she founded Fair Fight, a civil society organisation that educates young and minority voters on their voting rights. Come 2020 elections, Georgia saw a heavy turnout of voters — most of whom were newly registered, thanks to her efforts —who voted for Biden, effectively changing the direction of American politics in profound ways.



