In other words, Ms Abrams laid the foundation and the infrastructure to change voter patterns in the Deep South, setting the stage for Biden’s win.
After watching her documentary All In on Amazon Prime, I can only admire Abrams for her resilience. But what remains most important to me in this Abrams story is how she dealt with her failure.
We would have forgiven her is she chose to give up and walk away, but she is cut from a different cloth. She used her failure as a learning opportunity and a turnaround moment. What we are seeing in Georgia is a culmination of 10 years of backbreaking work that might never have materialised had she decided 2018 was the end.
And now, with this win and national recognition, Abrams is one of the most powerful Americans, even without an elective position and the definition of leading without a title. 
